      • lock

        public void lock()
        Safety lock the climber. No inputs will be passed to the motors while locked. When lock is called, all desired outputs will be reset to prevent the "HAL lag" effect

      • setArmMovementRate

        public void setArmMovementRate​(double rate)
        Set the desired arm movement rate. Positive values will move the arms downward. Keep in mind that this will not obey the arm holders' limits because we do not have sensors on the arms
        Parameters:
        rate - Movement rate to send to arms.

      • setCrawlRate

        public void setCrawlRate​(double rate)
        Sets the desired speed for the crawlers NOTE: Positive values move the robot forwards
        Parameters:
        rate - Movement speed for crawlers

      • setLegMovementRate

        public void setLegMovementRate​(double rate)
        Sets the desired speed for the legs. Will not push past low sensor. NOTE: Positive values push the legs down
        Parameters:
        rate - Speed to move the legs at
